#16026

```json
{
  "version": "0.2.0",
  "configurations": [
    {
      "name": "Chrome",
      "type": "chrome",
      "request": "launch",
      "url": "http://localhost:3000",
      "sourceMaps": true,
      "webRoot": "${workspaceRoot}/public"
    },
    {
      "type": "node",
      "request": "launch",
      "name": "Server",
      "program": "${workspaceRoot}/bin/www",
      "cwd": "${workspaceRoot}"
    }
  ],
  "compounds": [
    {
      "name": "App",
      "configurations": [
        "what"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

Starting the `App` compound will actually launch the `Chrome` configuration, although it mentions a fake `what` configuration.

There should be warning or error decorations for unknown configurations. It should also not pick a random one when starting.
